org.jtrim2.taskgraph

Interface TaskFactoryWrapper


  • public interface TaskFactoryWrapper
    Defines a task node factory wrapping another task node factory. The wrapper can do something before or after the actual factory, transform its result or even avoid calling the wrapped task node factory.
    See Also:
    TaskExecutorAop.wrapFactory(TaskFactoryDefiner, TaskFactoryWrapper)

    • Method Detail

      • createTaskNode

        <R,I> TaskFactory<R,I> createTaskNode(TaskFactoryProperties properties,
                                      TaskFactoryKey<R,I> factoryKey,
                                      TaskFactorySetup<R,I> wrapped)
                               throws java.lang.Exception
        Creates the task node factory relying on the given wrapped task node factory. The wrapped task node factory must be created by this method if it wants to actually execute the wrapped task node factory.
        Type Parameters:
        R - the return type of the task nodes created by this method
        I - the type of the task node factory argument available in nodeDef.factoryArg()
        Parameters:
        properties - the properties of the node factory to be created. This argument cannot be null.
        factoryKey - the factory key identifying the factory to be wrapped. This argument cannot be null.
        wrapped - the factory creating the wrapped task node factory doing the actual work. This argument cannot be null.
        Returns:
        the function executed by the task node to be created. This method may never return null.
        Throws:
        OperationCanceledException - thrown if the task detects that it was canceled (usually by checking the provided CancellationToken)
        java.lang.Exception - thrown if some irrecoverable error occurs. Note that such an exception usually means that the complete task graph execution will fail.
